Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Teisagoras. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 181, 28. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 322.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1078)
